Name: boringssl
URL: https://boringssl.googlesource.com/boringssl
Revision: e056f59c7dfdcf891af03bc7900c946ac485c78f
Upstream Revision: https://boringssl.googlesource.com/boringssl/+/e056f59c7dfdcf891af03bc7900c946ac485c78f/
Security Critical: yes

License File: src/LICENSE
  License: BSD-3-Clause, Copyright, ISC, MIT, Misc, OpenSSL

Description:
  A fork of OpenSSL, as described at https://www.imperialviolet.org/2014/06/20/boringssl.html
  Revision is from `git merge-base JIRI_HEAD origin/main`.
  Prerequisites: * apt install curl git golang perl python
  To update:
  1. Roll BoringSSL:
  ```
  go run $FUCHSIA_DIR/third_party/boringssl/roll_boringssl.go
  ```
  1. Test according to instructions given by the previous step.
  1. Commit, review, and submit the changes to this repository. Remind the reviewer in the commit message to independently verify the upstream URL, execute the roll and compare the roll outputs.
     A reviewer can sync to the same revision using
     ```
     go run $FUCHSIA_DIR/third_party/boringssl/roll_boringssl.go --commit <commit-ish>
     ```
